{"word":"H1690 - דְּבֵלָה - dᵉbêlâh - deb-ay-law' - Cake of figs","slug":"H1690","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">דְּבֵלָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>dᵉbêlâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>deb-ay-law'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Cake of figs"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D3;&#x05BC;&#x05D1;&#x05DC;&#x05D4; - d<sup>e</sup>be&#x0302;la&#x0302;h</b> - <i>deb-ay-law'</i><p/>From an unused root (akin to <a href=\"#/H2082\">H2082</a>) probably meaning to <i>press</i> together; a <i>cake</i> of pressed figs: - cake (lump) of figs."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1689\">H1689</a>, <a href=\"#/H1691\">H1691</a>"}]}